The chairman of the Senate Committee on Appropriations, Mohammed Danjuma Goje (APC, Gombe) has explained why he stepped down for Senate Leader Ahmad Lawan for the position of Senate President in the incoming 9th Assembly. Goje withdrew from the race and declared support for Lawan after meeting with President Muhammadu Buhari on Thursday. Goje later tweeted on his Twitter handle @mdgoje1 that he stepped down from Lawan for national interest and out of respect for President Buhari. “Today, during my meeting with President Buhari at the State House, Abuja. The meeting with the President led to my withdrawal from the Senate Presidency. “I took this hard decision in the interest of the country and out of my respect for the President,” Goje said. Senate Presidency: We appreciate Goje’s sacrifice—El Rufai Why I backed out of Senate Presidency race – Goje Inside ‘mad dash’ for Senate presidency Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin